2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with network bandwidth allocation and scheduling in the context of networked control systems. This is a relevant topic in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The proposed feedback scheduler is designed to work in dynamic environments, which may involve distributed and parallel computing. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics): Although the paper does not explicitly mention robotics, the proposed approach can be applied to control networks in robotics systems. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper involves the development of an integrated feedback scheduler, which may involve software engineering principles and practices.
